The Secretary to Ondo State Government, SSG, Ifedayo Abegunde has resigned his appointment from the government of Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu. Abegunde resigned on Monday morning. Abegunde confirmed his resignation via a telephone chat with DAILY POST. “Yes it is true. I have resigned my appointment as Ondo State SSG this morning. It is true my brother.” The SSG added that his next line of actions politically would be communicated within the next 24 hours.